The rally will zoom off outside its traditional starting point at the Kenyatta International Convention Centre (KICC) on June 24, a big plus for Kenya as the WRC Promoter will be able to capture the Nairobi skyline pictures portraying a modern metropolis, before the 50 competitors head to the Kasarani Stadium for side-by-side racing in the four-kilometre Super Special Stage.
This is the perfect opportunity for rally fans residing in Nairobi and neighbouring areas to watch the action from close quarters.



