It is advisable for the fans to arrive early on Friday and head to the designated spectator zones as the rest of the Safari route will be closed for the public.
This will be a day-long of activities and perfect family outing as the drivers will repeat Soysambu, Elmentaita and Sleeping Warrior sections twice before returning to Naivasha.
To say Soysambu will be easy is an understatement.There are many speed traps to slow drivers.
However, the Sleeping Warrior Hill, named the same as it resembles a warrior sleeping, has all the ingredients of the old Safari —  rocky and hilly. Elmentaita, which ends by the lake side, is a new addition and extremely rocky in some sections before ending in the buffalo and giraffe’s kingdom.
This section will sell Kenya as a tourism destination in global television to an estimated 70 million audience. It will be a marketing coup which cannot be recreated in foreign tourism exhibition.
It is from this perspective that the Kenya Tourism Board and Magical Kenya should milk the Safari as an addition of their traditional packages.
The Safari format has changed over time as the FIA has given safety premium consideration.



